{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Grease four ramekins (Ø 8 cm) then set aside.","Cut asparagus spears from stalks and set aside. Cut stalks into pieces.","Place asparagus stalk pieces and chives in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add butter and lemon juice then cook <nobr>1 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add milk, eggs, salt and pepper then mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>.","Add smoked salmon and stir in <nobr>5 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer to prepared ramekins then gently arrange asparagus spears on top. Place in Varoma dish.","Place water in mixing bowl then place Varoma into position. Steam <nobr>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Serve immediately in ramekins."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["20 g butter, plus extra for greasing","120 g asparagus, woody ends removed","1 small handful fresh chives (approx. 5 g), cut in lengths (2 cm)","1 Tbsp lemon juice","30 g milk","8 medium eggs","½ tsp fine sea salt","¼ tsp ground black pepper","80 g smoked salmon, cut in thin strips","600 g water, for steaming"]}],"id":"r94086","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-1dNYbMDuATY\/XZaeSlmkDnI\/AAAAAAAAgks\/_5tTZIh2RhUN2TKKoC0kAv8377CNPfjWACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_TgEF2Mn-D1-Y351V.png","title":"Potted Eggs with Salmon and Asparagus","publishedAt":"2015-12-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"18.8 g","fat":"16.6 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"1.1 g","calories":"956 kJ \/ 229 kcal"},"usefulItems":"4 ramekins (Ø 8 cm)","hintsAndTricks":["A wonderfully simple-to-prepare yet impressive brunch dish, steamed in the Varoma. Particularly enjoyable around late spring or early summer when British asparagus is in season. Also makes a nice lunch served with a side salad.","To serve 2, halve all ingredients and steam two ramekins above 400 g water in step 7."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","30m","4 portions"]}